{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"69f32a87-7373-49be-affa-c0b8f911721f","content":"There's nothing in this repository about MAUI safe areas, so I'll answer from my knowledge of .NET MAUI APIs:\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` — Yes, this is correct.** This is a platform-specific property (`Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific.Page.UseSafeAreaProperty`) that insets your page content to avoid the notch/Dynamic Island. It remains valid in .NET 10.\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` — No, this doesn't exist as a built-in property.** There is no `IgnoreSafeArea` attached property on `Grid` or any layout in .NET MAUI. Your tutorial may be outdated or referencing a community library.\n\n**To make a background image extend behind the safe area**, the typical approach is:\n\n1. Set `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` (or omit it) on the page.\n2. Use a full-bleed `Image` with `Aspect=\"AspectFill\"` as the first child in your layout.\n3. Wrap your *content* in a layout that respects safe area padding manually, or use a nested layout with `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` only on a content section.\n\nAlternatively, place the image at the page level and overlay a `Grid` with manual `Padding` matching the safe area insets via platform code.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"348f74fd-a99a-4b9a-bd74-a569827daaff","outputTokens":395,"requestId":"502B:2BEA6E:1D413C2:206A32D:69FA9339"},"id":"768c07c2-9eec-4404-b03f-60d9009501c0","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:02:59.321Z","parentId":"bad117db-da8f-4beb-ba67-d595d4253285"}
